content: निस्तॄ {c1c} <ab>P.</ab> {@--1@} To pass through, cross over (<ab>fig.</ab> also); निस्तीर्णा प्रतिज्ञासरित <ls>Mu. 1</ls>; <ls>Bh. 3. 4</ls>; <ls>Ve. 6. 36.</ls> {@--2@} To fulfil, accomplish. {@--3@} To pass or get over, surmount, overcome; धनैरापदं मानवा निस्तरंति <ls>Subhāṣ.</ls>; <ls>R. 3. 7.</ls> {@--4@} To complete, go to the end of; <ls>R. 14. 21.</ls> {@--5@} To pass or spend (as a time). {@--6@} To expiate, atone for. {@--7@} To get out of, escape, be saved from. {%--<ab>Caus.</ab>%} {@--1@} To deliver, rescue, save. {@--2@} To overcome, surmount.
